  "title": "Daily Report - 2026-06-16",
  "categories": {
    "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion and Development Updates",
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "In the general discussion channel, community members exchanged casual greetings throughout the day. A user named ross inquired about whether orders were still being taken for humanoid robots, referencing a news article with a dead link mentioning an amount of 420,000. Odilitime responded that the idea had been started but fell apart. A developer named Ginga asked if anyone was looking to hire a developer. Inhuman Resources shared a Web3 trivia game post promoting an online learning platform with multiple categories, describing it as a safe and fun space for everyone. Ross also shared an episode of the Cron Job series titled The Orchestrator Awakens covering the week of May 31 to June 6, 2026, which highlighted ElizaOS launching a coding workbench achieving parity with Claude Code and Codex, a production outage affecting Eliza Cloud login, the decomposition of the monolithic plugin-lifeops into seven modular plugins, and a surge of DeFAI builders joining the ecosystem.",
        "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
        "images": [
          "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/2066698024126951893_2156c3b5.jpg",
          "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/embed-thumbnail-1516311446135378023_eb12b438.jpg"
        ],
        "videos": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/snmysusiqq0-start-69_df8dd4fd.mp4"
      },
      {
        "text": "In the coders channel, activity was minimal with community members Solify and bobjonesgood exchanging brief greetings. The channel topic directs users to the official ElizaOS documentation at docs.elizaos.ai to get started with building agents.",
